## Technical documentation

### Publication

Harris, L.R., Adams, J.B., Dayaram, A., Dunga, L.V., Job, N., Kirkman, S.P., Lamberth, S.J., Pfaff, M.C., Raw, J.L., Rishworth, G.M., Robbins, A., Sink, K.J., Skowno, A.L., van Deventer, H., van Niekerk, L., 2025. **Cross-realm biodiversity profile of the South African coastal zone**. African Journal of Marine Science 47, 1-18. [https://doi.org/10.2989/1814232X.2025.2463342](https://doi.org/10.2989/1814232X.2025.2463342){.uri target="_blank"}\
*Description of the different types of coastal ecosystem types and broad biodiversity patterns in the South African coastal zone. The supplementary material includes a glossary of terms, guidance regarding map layers to use, and a table of the ecosystem types and their areas.*

### Data availability

The following datasets are available for download:

1.  [**Map of coastal ecosystem types / ecologically determined coastal zone**](https://bgis.sanbi.org/Projects/Detail/213){target="_blank"}

2.  [**Dune base line**](https://bgis.sanbi.org/SpatialDataset/Detail/3694){target="_blank"}: proxy representation of a decadal-scale high-water mark and recommended ecological line to represent the 'coastline'

3.  [**Landmass line**](https://dwa.maps.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=9d139e8cbe4248e3ba389aa7fbd3af54){target="_blank"}: recognized administrative boundary of the South African mainland landmass

### Related publications and supporting information

1.  [**South African National Ecosystem Classification System (SA-NECS)**](https://bgis.sanbi.org/Projects/Detail/1237)**\
    ***Details on South Africa's ecosystem classification system, with a link to download the SA-NECS handbook*

2.  Dunga, L., Lück-Vogel, M., Blamey, L.K., Bolton, J., Rothman, M., Desmet, P., Sink, K., 2024. **Mapping South Africa's canopy-forming kelp forests using low-cost, high-resolution Sentinel-2 imagery**. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science 310, 108989. [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ecss.2024.108989](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ecss.2024.108989){.uri target="_blank"}\
    *Technical details regarding the mapping of kelp forests using remote imagery*

